The paper focuses on analyzing deep networks for image classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses measures of importance for neurons and how they contribute to the network's classification outcome, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes an algorithm for automatically labeling patches of the input image that activate important neurons, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses how the network decomposes an image to make its final classification, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
